In [62]:
fig = plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
fig.suptitle('Confidence Interval, Standard Deviation, Estimate')

# subplot(number_of_rows, number_of_columns, plot_number)
line1 = fig.add_subplot(2, 2, 1)
sns.lineplot(x=seattle_temps.date, y=seattle_temps.temp, ci=95, ax=line1).set_title('confidence interval = 95')

line2 = fig.add_subplot(2, 2, 2)
sns.lineplot(x=seattle_temps.date, y=seattle_temps.temp, ci='sd', ax=line2).set_title('ci = standard deviation')

line3 = fig.add_subplot(2, 2, 3)
sns.lineplot(x=seattle_temps.date, y=seattle_temps.temp, ci=None, ax=line3).set_title('ci = None')

# if estimator None, all observations will be drawn
line4 = fig.add_subplot(2, 2, 4)
sns.lineplot(x=seattle_temps.date, y=seattle_temps.temp, estimator=None, ax=line4).set_title('estimator = None')

fig.autofmt_xdate(rotation=90)

Categorical Plots catplot¶

Figure-level interface for drawing categorical plots onto a FacetGrid.

kinds include: point, bar

Note, when using certain plots such as catplot, data must be passed using 'x', 'y'
